- cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely category as the paper deals with achievable rate regions and capacity of a class of interference channels. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is also likely as the paper discusses a broadcast interference channel and its capacity region. 
- cs.SI (Signal Processing) is relevant as the paper deals with Gaussian interference channels and their achievable rate regions. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is a possibility as the paper discusses a class of broadcast channels, which can be used for multimedia transmission. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is less likely as the paper does not focus on complexity analysis, but rather on achievable rate regions and capacity of a communication channel.
